replies.body:
I am traumatized to this day about this experience, so this is going to be hard for me to say ;_;

I was playing as Amumu {{champion:32}}  (It was either S2 or S3), running around the purple side blue buff jungle area, when suddenly their Volibear {{champion:106}}  and bot lane shows up. I work it out in my head to run towards the tri bush and then flash {{summoner:4}}  over the wall into the river. I make it to the wall, Volibear charging at me on all fours, ready to flip me into his allies. I smash D and flash over the wall, thinking that I have luckily escaped Voli's wrath. I was terribly, terribly wrong. As I'm flashing, Volibear scoops his arms into the ground in front of him and throws them up into the air. Even though I had managed to flash the wall, that dreaded flip had somehow connected onto me the split second before I flashed. The next two seconds were the longest seconds of my life. I watched myself successfully flash over the wall, only to get flipped back over the wall into the enemy jungle and champions. I could do nothing but cry {{champion:32}} {{item:3070}} as Volibear and his allies made quick work of me.

This experience haunts me every time I play against a Volibear now ;_;
